<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <!-- Set the title of the html -->
    <title>Ametrine.host</title>
    <!-- Set the favicon -->
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="../images/favicon.png" />
    <!-- Meta tags -->
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta
      name="viewport"
      content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, viewport-fit=cover"
    />
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Powerful server hosting starting at €0.75/GB. We're a transparent hosting provider with a 100% uptime and reliable support."
    />
    <!-- APPLE -->
    <!-- Apple Touch Icon (at least 200x200px) -->
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="../images/apple-touch-icon.png" />
    <!-- To run web application in full-screen -->
    <meta name="apple-mobile-web-app-capable" content="yes" />
    <!-- Status Bar Style-->
    <meta name="apple-mobile-web-app-status-bar-style" content="black" />
    <!-- END OF APPLE -->
    <!-- Microsoft Tiles -->
    <meta name="msapplication-config" content="browserconfig.xml" />
    <!--STYLESHEETS-->
    <!--Asynchronous load-->
    <link 
      rel="stylesheet" 
      href="https://use.fontawesome.com/releases/v5.15.3/css/all.css" 
      integrity="sha384-SZXxX4whJ79/gErwcOYf+zWLeJdY/qpuqC4cAa9rOGUstPomtqpuNWT9wdPEn2fk" 
      crossorigin="anonymous"
      media="print" 
      onload="this.media='all'">
    <noscript>
      <link
        rel="stylesheet"
        href="https://use.fontawesome.com/releases/v5.15.3/css/all.css"
      />
    </noscript>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Ubuntu:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,700;1,300;1,400;1,500;1,700&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <!--Synchronous load-->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="../css/business.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/flickity@2/dist/flickity.min.css">
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://unpkg.com/flickity@2/dist/flickity.min.css"
    />
  </head>

  <body>
    <%~ E.includeFile('../templates/preloader.eta') %>
    <%~ E.includeFile('../templates/navbar.eta') %>
    <header id="header">
      <div>
        <span>
          <h1>So, what's our business plan?</h1>
          <h2 class="subtitle">Read about our values, commitments and plans.</h2>
        </span>
        <span>
            <img alt="laptop" src="../images/svg/link.svg" height="400px" width="400px">
        </span>
      </div>
    </header>
    <div class="divider"></div>
    <main id="main">
      <h2>Our values</h2>
      <div>
        <div class="about">
          <h3>Honesty</h3>
          <p>
            We are honest to our clients, regardless of the situation. We communicate problems with clients,
            and we try to resolve them as soon as possible with the best solution possible.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="about">
          <h3>Trust</h3>
          <p>
            We want to build a company, which you can trust, regardless of your current standing with us.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>
    <section class="mapSection">
      <div class="divider2"></div>
      <h2>Our commitments</h2>
      <h3>We are commited to maintain...</h3>
      <div class="cardWrapper">
          <div class="about">
          <h3><i class="fa fa-lock"></i> Data Privacy</h3>
          <p>
            We won't sell, share, or use your data in a malicious way.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="about">
          <h3><i class="fa fa-tree"></i> Minimum carbon footprint</h3>
          <p>
            Our servers are hosted in datacenters with little to or no carbon footprint.
          </p>
        </div>
                <div class="about">
          <h3><i class="fa fa-coins"></i> Maximum Performance</h3>
          <p>
            We balance the load between our nodes evenly, as to not oversell a node.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="about">
          <h3><i class="fa fa-coins"></i> Minimum profitability</h3>
          <p>
            Our VPS nodes have a maximum profitability of only €10/Mo.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <div class="divider3"></div>
    <section class="plansWrapper">
      <span>
        <div class="plans">
          <h2>Our Plans?</h2>
          <p class="skipMargin">
            Once we reach a sustainable profit margin, we plan on:
          </p>
          <h3>Giving Back</h3>
          <p>
            We'll donate up to 75% of profits earned in a Month every 3 Months towards random charities around the world.
            You'll be able to decide, which one it's gonna be.
          </p>
          <h3>Getting more locations around the world</h3>
          <p>
            So your project can continue expanding all around the world.
          </p>
          <h3>Providing more services</h3>
          <p>
            From Discord bot hosting, to game specific servers - all at an affordable price.
          </p>
        </div>
        
      </span>
    </section>
    <summary>
      <h2>Sounds too good to be true, so who are you?</h2>
      <h3>We're Ametrine.host</h3>
      <p>We're a group of passionate people who <b>love</b> helping others. 
      We operate on tight profit margins, so you can pay less for essential hosting services. Yes, we admit it. It might be crazy to operate 
      at such small profit margins, but we want to prove to the world it's possible to own a transparent, independent, open-source, low-profit
      hosting company.
      While we can't guarantee all our plans will come true, we'll do our best to at least <i>try as hard as we can</i>.</p>
    </summary>
    <footer>
      <p>© 2021 Ametrine.host</p>
    </footer>
    <%~ E.includeFile('../templates/backtotop.eta') %>
    <script src="https://unpkg.com/flickity@2/dist/flickity.pkgd.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://unpkg.com/@popperjs/core@2"></script>
    <script src="https://unpkg.com/tippy.js@6"></script>
    <script src="../js/tooltips.js"></script>
    <script src="../js/flickity.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
